& [AttentionRuntimeRegistry071] is the realized semantic-stack-frame registry
  + [moment] is focus refinement needs a live registry that tracks active attention like program stack frames, but in semantic attention terms
  + [focus] is attention runtime registry
  + [inside] is attention_stack_frame, semantic_register_set, parent_frame, child_frame_set, return_anchor, frame_operation, frame_state, frame_trace, and frame_outside
  + [boundary] is visible SOP state approximation for attention, not hidden LLM internals or native hard-coded stack frames
  + [outside] is hidden activations, exact transformer attention, model weights, executable runtime implementation, and untracked cognition
  + [wisdom] is the registry fits because focus needs inspectable live state to prevent drift, stale frames, and lost returns
  + [caution] is the registry must not overclaim access to internal model state; it records visible semantic state only
  + [balance] is improved because push, return, close, and outside preservation reduce focus leaks and periphery flood
  + [next_step] is use the registry with FocusResolutionRefinement to keep a live current attention runtime state frame

  = must: keep frame state visible and semantic
  = must: close or return frames rather than leaving them stale
  = should: use the registry as the running substrate for focus_quality and integration_receipt work

